    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="490"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/9187: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-23T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 23, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 23—2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>151. Secret for the President. Pursuant to your authorization<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d490fn3">Contained in President Wilson’s undated telegram No. 16 to
                        Colonel House, <ref target="frus1919Parisv01#pg_136">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 136</ref>.</note> I requested General
                    Pershing to detail such officer in his command as he considered most competent
                    to undertake the work of estimating the damage done by the Germans in Belgium
                    and northern France on account of which reparation should be required from
                    Germany. General Pershing has detailed for this work Brigadier General C. H.
                    McKinstry. I have conferred with General McKinstry and have asked him to advise
                    me after he has considered the problem how he believes this work [should?] be
                    done.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
